                                              John Terry permanent captain  Watford: John Terry of Chelsea was named as England rsquo;s permanent captain by coach Fabio Capello on Tuesday.   Terry, 27, was given the job he held under former coach Steve McClaren and will lead the team out against Czech Republic in Wednesday rsquo;s friendly at Wembley when he wins his 45th cap.  ldquo;It means the world to me to retain the armband, rdquo; said Terry who was told by Italian Capello that he would be captain after England rsquo;s training session on Tuesday morning.
  Manchester United rsquo;s Rio Ferdinand, who was in the running to take over as skipper, has been appointed vice-captain.   Bindra booty   New Delhi: Olympic gold medallist Abhinav Bindra would be awarded a prize money of Rs 50 lakh by the government during the Arjuna Awards ceremony which will be held on August 29.   The government on Tuesday formally announced the Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna Award and Arjuna Awards for the year 2007. Dhyan Chand awards for the year 2008 and Dronacharya awards for the year 2007 were also announced here.   The list of awardees   Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna Award 2007: Mahendra Singh Dhoni (Cricket); Arjuna Awards 2007: Chitra K. Soman (Athletics), Anup Sridhar (Badminton), Johnson Varghese (Boxing), Harika Dronavalli (Chess), Arjun Atwal (Golf), Probhjot Singh (Hockey), Tombi Devi (Judo), Bajranglal Takhar (Rowing), Avneet Kaur Sidhu (Shooting), Alka Tomar (Wrestling), Farman Basha (Power Lifting (Disabled Category); Dhyan Chand 2008: Hakam Singh (Athletics), Mukhbain Singh (Hockey), Gian Singh (Wrestling); Dronacharya Awards 2007: Sanjeeva Kumar Singh (Archery), Jagdish Singh (Boxing), G.E. Sridharan (Volley Ball), Jagminder Singh (Wrestling).   Minotra dies   New Delhi: Former Indian Davis Cupper and Asian Championship winning tennis player Shyam Minotra on Tuesday passed away after prolonged illness. He was 62.   Md. Sp. win   Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting paddlers defeated Stag International 4-2 in Tuesday rsquo;s round of table tennis matches of the ONGC Bengal Premier League. Soumyajeet Ghosh and Subham Choudhury won their rubbers for Mohammedan Sporting.   Dalmiya visit   Calcutta: The Cricket Association of Bengal president Jagmohan Dalmiya, along with two joint and assistant secretaries, on Tuesday visited the proposed site for the cricket academy at Haldia. ldquo;This is a nice place... The facilities are fine, matching the guidelines of the BCCI, and if everything goes according to our plan, the academy will soon come up here, rdquo; an official said.
                                                                                                                                                                 
